<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-164-176 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 706 765</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Technology  May 1991 v7 n5 p101(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Mandamp;T Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Luxcom educates hub. (LC100 Series 2000 Universal Smart Hub)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Luxcom (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Luxcom LC100 Series 2000 Universal Smart Hub (Network hub)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionNetwork Hubs.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Luxcom Inc. has announced the LC100 Series 2000 Universal Smart Hub, anintelligent unit that lets users connect LANs, WANS, and terminal networks.andO;Based on Luxcom's Universal Premises Network architecture, the UniversalSmart Hub is designed to meet users' current and long-term requirements,which might include new network protocols, combining voice and datacommunication on the same network, and high-speed communications.andM;The Universal Smart Hub is a modular, intelligent hub that provides a varietyof protocol interfaces from a single platform without requiring a bridge.andP;  Itoffers a 100-Mbit/sec fiber-optic backbone to support Ethernet and token ringLAN communications.andP;  The product also handles RS-232/422, IBM 3270, T1, T3,and ISDN on the same fiberoptic backbone.andP;  Luxcom's Universal PremisesNetwork architecture is implemented at the physical layer to ensure protocoltransparency.andP;  The hub uses a universal bus to directly connect any twoprotocols in a network, rather than using a separate bus for each protocol.andM;Ethernet support is 10Base-T-compliant.andP;  Token ring, both 4- and 16-Mbit/sec,is supported over unshielded and shielded twisted-pair wire.andP;  The UniversalSmart Hub includes network management hardware built into each hub.andP;  Thishardware can be accessed by installing Luxcom's LC100 Network Managementsoftware, which includes SNMP support and allows the hub to manage networksfrom a single workstation.andP;  The LC100 Series 2000 Universal Smart Hub pricesstart at  4,995.andP;  Ethernet and token ring configurations are priced at $260per port and $165 per port, respectively.andP;  Contact Luxcom Inc., 3848 BayCenter Place, Hayward, CA 94545; 415-786-1200.andO;</TEXT></DOC>